The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 07 July is 46,305 (5,359.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 02 July, there were 1,431 new confirmed cases (165.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 25 June, there were 775 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 85% (656 extra cases).
